whereas.text:
Whereas, in 2013, approximately 22,240 new cases of
			 ovarian cancer will be diagnosed and 14,030 women will die of ovarian cancer in
			 the United States;

Whereas the mortality rate for ovarian cancer has not
			 significantly decreased since the War on Cancer was declared 40
			 years ago;

Whereas the relative 5-year survival rate is 44 percent,
			 although survival rates vary depending on the stage of cancer at the time of
			 diagnosis;

Whereas the lack of a reliable early detection test means
			 that approximately 75 percent of cases of ovarian cancer are detected at an
			 advanced stage;

Whereas all women are at risk for ovarian cancer, and 90
			 percent of women diagnosed with ovarian cancer do not have a family history
			 that puts them at a higher risk;
